Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.03,0:00:05.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rhythm of the wind clarifies all reasoning...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.78,0:00:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And causes alibi tricks to fall apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.91,0:00:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter who looks at the case, we're sure to find the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.66,0:00:11.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the truth is in the massage point!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.66,0:00:13.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.12,0:00:15.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.00,0:00:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.21,0:01:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As we were on our way home..
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.13,0:01:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Driving down a mountain road, shrouded in fog...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.13,0:01:50.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle's car broke down once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.30,0:01:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, we found help nearby...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.35,0:01:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the Kuron Health Appliances Company's training facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.73,0:02:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, the one-man president of the company, Umetani Shiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.27,0:02:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Held an in-company competition to see who could design the most relaxing chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.49,0:02:13.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But as Umetani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was deciding the winner, he was suddenly stabbed with one of his own knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.33,0:02:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And although Umetani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} luckily escaped with his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.50,0:02:22.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the culprit, sped away from the scene in his car...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.50,0:02:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only to careen off the side of a cliff and plummet to his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.55,0:02:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the accident occurred, the fog was very thick...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.34,0:02:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with the sharp curve here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.97,0:02:39.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably lost control during his escape and plummeted to his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.98,0:02:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's the most likely scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.81,0:02:44.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.48,0:02:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are just too many strange things about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.53,0:02:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here we have a man who stabbed someone out of rage...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.57,0:02:53.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And punctured other cars' tires so no one would be able to pursue him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.82,0:03:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, he loses control of his steering wheel during his escape, and crashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.96,0:03:05.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curve mirror that had its direction changed...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.34,0:03:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The brake fluid that had been drained..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.72,0:03:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something... There's definitely something...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.60,0:03:20.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Cigar Case of Good Fortune:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.60,0:03:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part 2!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.19,0:03:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First things first... Umetani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please go get checked up at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.36,0:03:31.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll question you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.20,0:03:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there's no need for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.74,0:03:38.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now, I have to decide what the future direction of this company will be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.54,0:03:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umetani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.92,0:03:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really should go to the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.00,0:03:49.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? This is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.46,0:03:54.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the cigar case I had in my pocket hadn't saved my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.26,0:03:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would already be in the other world by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.34,0:03:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think about it like that..
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.81,0:04:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right, this really is a cigar case of good fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.02,0:04:06.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is horrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.06,0:04:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything inside was crushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.23,0:04:11.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sure are an unusual type of tobacco.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.57,0:04:14.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say Mister, how many of those do you smoke a day?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.32,0:04:18.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see... Probably about 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.45,0:04:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it must be very hard for you now that you don't have cigarettes to smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.74,0:04:23.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'd like, I can give you mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.41,0:04:24.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.16,0:04:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have some more in my car, and besides, I only smoke cigars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.92,0:04:32.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.17,0:04:34.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, would like to try to smoke one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.09,0:04:36.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cigar?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.13,0:04:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... Shouldn't we be focusing on the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.81,0:04:42.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I almost forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.31,0:04:44.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have something that might be useful to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.23,0:04:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something useful?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.23,0:04:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I have a video of what happened while I was in my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.94,0:04:53.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A video? Then, could it be that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.57,0:04:55.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.95,0:05:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It most likely shows what happened when Hiramatsu stabbed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.24,0:05:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yokomizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.41,0:05:07.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, please come to the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.42,0:05:08.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.58,0:05:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.09,0:05:18.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found this tucked inside the futons in Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room on the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.14,0:05:24.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A rope, a stun gun and a will...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.68,0:05:26.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A will?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.06,0:05:27.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does it say
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.81,0:05:31.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! W-What the hell does this mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.69,0:05:32.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.69,0:05:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.36,0:05:37.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I have lost the confidence that kept me working in this company.'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.74,0:05:39.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Please forgive my selfishness."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.74,0:05:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Kuron Health Appliances Company President, Umetani Shiro."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.41,0:05:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.87,0:05:48.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is President Umetani's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.37,0:05:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.38,0:05:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who wrote this piece of nonsense?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.38,0:05:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no reason to commit suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.92,0:05:57.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought as much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.26,0:06:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} probably planned to kill you and use this to make it look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.18,0:06:05.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-How could he...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.68,0:06:08.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're most likely not mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.56,0:06:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's watch the video first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.06,0:06:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A while back, I installed security cameras to prevent our product designs from being stolen...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.65,0:06:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I never thought they would be needed for something like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.91,0:06:22.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There sure are a lot of ugly things out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.74,0:06:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is the part!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.70,0:06:31.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others left the room, I tested the Aimuzu myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.17,0:06:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that one's great, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.21,0:06:37.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes; there's no doubt that it's the most comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.51,0:06:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I came upon a problem...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.59,0:06:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.22,0:06:45.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted me to allow him to resign.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.14,0:06:48.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, he wouldn't allow me to market the Aimuzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.73,0:06:55.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even programmed the chair to self-destruct if he didn't input the password into it before midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.94,0:06:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you..
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.48,0:07:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew I could make a huge profit off of the Aimuzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.32,0:07:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I was afraid that if I allowed him to resign...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.37,0:07:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would develop something even better than the Aimuzu for one of our competitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.00,0:07:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you chose to keep Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.08,0:07:18.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first, it looked like he understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.13,0:07:23.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he suddenly turned violent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.22,0:07:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I passed out from shock after he stabbed my shoulder, so I don't know what happened after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.94,0:07:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only regained consciousness...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.48,0:07:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others woke me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.65,0:07:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, afraid that he'd be discovered by everyone, fled through the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.28,0:07:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, he had everything prepared to make it look like a suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.96,0:07:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then grabbed a knife off the wall and stabbed him with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.79,0:07:57.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because he was always an impatient man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.63,0:08:05.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a bad personality...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.97,0:08:07.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nakano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.73,0:08:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.86,0:08:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is where Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s car was parked.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.41,0:08:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.16,0:08:33.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some brake fluid dripped on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.00,0:08:36.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means someone removed the connector tube.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.13,0:08:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, please try one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.96,0:08:45.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flavor isn't the same as a cigarette.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.84,0:08:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, go ahead and try one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.05,0:08:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't mind if I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.43,0:08:52.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's a splendid-looking cigar case.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.31,0:08:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is a souvenir from my parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.89,0:08:58.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the only one like it in the whole world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.52,0:09:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.82,0:09:01.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.65,0:09:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're sure this is Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s attache case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.45,0:09:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, there's no mistaking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.49,0:09:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's just like Hiramatsu to have hidden it in a closet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.75,0:09:16.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.96,0:09:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, he has a hobby of being very secretive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.58,0:09:22.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Development Department 3 is comprised of a single room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.09,0:09:26.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He always locks the door when he leaves and never lets anyone else in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.01,0:09:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when we're talking with him, he acts the same way as he did during the competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.01,0:09:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why did Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} want to kill the president?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.43,0:09:36.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How the hell are we supposed to know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.81,0:09:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, we're the ones who wanted to kill the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.40,0:09:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.36,0:09:43.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.19,0:09:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I meant to say that we understand his desire to work independently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.49,0:09:48.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.57,0:09:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just remembered that he got yelled at this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.91,0:09:57.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s Aimuzu was the only chair to arrive here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.83,0:10:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the president stormed into Development Department 3...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.54,0:10:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we eavesdropped on what was being said.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.13,0:10:08.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's when Hiramatsu ran out of the room and went somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.55,0:10:11.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honestly, he was reprimanded pretty harshly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.89,0:10:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And later on, when we found Hiramatsu and saw him heading back to the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.72,0:10:19.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time the president wasn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.19,0:10:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying that he wasn't satisfied, and had to cool down for a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.23,0:10:26.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took a break and went to buy the cheap cigar case that he was carrying earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.32,0:10:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder what got into him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.07,0:10:33.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, didn't everyone drive somewhere in their cars today?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.91,0:10:35.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle, nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.54,0:10:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we all went out to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.25,0:10:41.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, Hiramatsu didn't come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.67,0:10:44.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president returned by himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.21,0:10:46.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I came back in Nagano's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.55,0:10:50.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that must have been who we saw just before we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.47,0:10:51.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.59,0:10:54.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's what happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.80,0:10:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand everything now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.81,0:11:00.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? It's already this late, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.85,0:11:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'd like to thank you for cooperating in our questioning...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.94,0:11:06.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.07,0:11:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, if your car isn't repaired yet, I'll drive you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.28,0:11:14.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Thanks for always helping us out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.75,0:11:22.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't I test this relaxing seat one more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.08,0:11:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.17,0:11:27.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This case wasn't a big deal, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.68,0:11:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on... What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.47,0:11:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, call Inspector Yokomizo and the others back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.39,0:11:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death was no accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.31,0:11:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is an ingeniously disguised murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.99,0:11:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s accident was a disguised murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.16,0:12:00.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.20,0:12:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While it's true that the brakes went out...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.04,0:12:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. Even if the brakes somehow failed...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.67,0:12:10.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That doesn't necessarily mean the driver would get in an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.13,0:12:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the culprit had already set a second trap to be sure he would get in a fatal accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.81,0:12:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.39,0:12:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thinking he had succeeded in killing the president, Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} fled by car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.36,0:12:35.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that thick fog, he sped down the mountain in a car with no brakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.28,0:12:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he was startled by the headlights of a car coming from the other direction...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.13,0:12:53.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lost control of his steering whee...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.63,0:12:56.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And plummeted off the side of the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.26,0:12:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a minute, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.64,0:13:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a car coming from the opposite direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.89,0:13:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a single, ascending road which connects to the side road leading to the company training facility...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.89,0:13:07.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And continues until it leads to a dead end at the top of the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was also dark with a thick fog at the time, so there wouldn't have been any pedestrians.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.36,0:13:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, a car driving up in those conditions...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.36,0:13:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.87,0:13:23.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The light he thought was coming from the opposite direction...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.75,0:13:26.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was actually coming from the headlights of his own car.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.87,0:13:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if there wasn't anything ahead of him, then what could have...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.88,0:13:34.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.30,0:13:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember anything at the scene of the accident which may have reflected a source of light?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.22,0:13:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.22,0:13:46.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the private road leading to the company training facility: the corner mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.93,0:13:48.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.81,0:13:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By changing the angle of that corner mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.15,0:13:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone made his headlights be reflected back at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.73,0:14:00.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The officer in charge of road maintenance here said that its angle was correct this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.28,0:14:09.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in this facility's parking lot, there are traces of a fluid in the space where Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had his car parked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.37,0:14:16.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, that means the same person drained the brake fluid and punctured the other car tires.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.17,0:14:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because even if he drained the brake fluid, there was still the possibility that Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could take another car.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.72,0:14:29.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he had been pursued by other cars, he could have been stopped before the accident occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.19,0:14:32.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.52,0:14:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The person who committed the crime works with this company?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.73,0:14:37.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This company? Surely you're not talking about us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.78,0:14:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.95,0:14:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible, because we were never alone long enough to have been able to do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.49,0:14:45.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, except for the president, that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.62,0:14:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fool, I'm the victim here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.91,0:14:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, Umetani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.29,0:14:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were alone after the competition, saying you needed to take a break to smoke a cigar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.67,0:15:00.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, didn't you return alone after everyone went out to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.17,0:15:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, you must driven by the corner mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.51,0:15:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, you forgot something important!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.64,0:15:12.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and one more thing... The culprit had a tool to help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.81,0:15:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what would that tool be?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.82,0:15:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "one more thing" that he had was...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.40,0:15:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was..
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.57,0:15:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.12,0:15:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fog?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.24,0:15:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the fog is a characteristic of this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.96,0:15:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without the fog, the fact that the corner mirror had been moved would have been discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.17,0:15:43.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the fog was the one essential thing required for this murder plan to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.26,0:15:48.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And only one person could have known about the fog in order to use it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.52,0:15:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,President Umetani..
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.89,0:15:53.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,President Umetani... It can only be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.48,0:15:55.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What is this nonsense?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.77,0:15:57.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fog is a natural phenomenon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.52,0:16:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And anyway, I couldn't have predicted that Hiramatsu would stab me and flee!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.28,0:16:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just cut the crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.03,0:16:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, you already knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.24,0:16:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You already knew that Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was about to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.87,0:16:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.17,0:16:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before you came here this morning, you had an argument with Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.59,0:16:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ran out of the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.97,0:16:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you were alone in the room, didn't you discover it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.89,0:16:31.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents of the attache case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.27,0:16:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You then thought about how to counter his plan, so you left to buy a cigar case before going out to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.11,0:16:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is because your usual one is a really important souvenir from your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.28,0:16:48.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it normal to use different ones depending on my mood?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.78,0:16:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then can you explain why someone like you, who smokes about 40 cigars a day...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.50,0:16:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bought a cigar case that can only hold four or five cigars at the most?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.17,0:17:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after arriving here...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.05,0:17:09.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You came up with a reason to delay the competition until night, when the fog would appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.10,0:17:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the one thing even the one-man president couldn't do...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.77,0:17:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is conjure up the fog needed for your murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.44,0:17:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You forgot something important that even a great detective needs...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.23,0:17:26.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't these all suppositions?! Where's your proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.90,0:17:30.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The proof is on the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.33,0:17:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please look carefully at Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s facial expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.46,0:17:41.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Umetani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had to choose one of the two options Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} gave him...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.46,0:17:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he decided to keep Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on-staff and forfeit the right to market the Aimuzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.68,0:17:49.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.30,0:17:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, stop here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.76,0:17:59.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why is Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} smiling even though his request was denied?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.15,0:18:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.31,0:18:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is... Haven't you actually granted his request?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.45,0:18:09.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please continue playing the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.62,0:18:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he started to tell you something...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.20,0:18:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was most likely the password.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.79,0:18:25.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The password that deactivates the program that makes the Aimuzu self-destruct.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.97,0:18:33.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he suddenly became infuriated and stabbed your shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.01,0:18:40.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He likely understood that you were lying when you accepted his conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.90,0:18:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey... Can you stop making things up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.31,0:18:48.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you just adding your own words to the video so that it fits your deductions?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.74,0:18:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really don't have any solid evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.49,0:18:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there's another part of this video which contradicts your testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.62,0:18:58.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another contradiction?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.62,0:19:00.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please continue playing the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.42,0:19:01.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.92,0:19:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.71,0:19:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You told us that you had lost consciousness after he stabbed your shoulder...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.55,0:19:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So why does it look like Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} stopped leaving because someone told him to?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.93,0:19:15.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.76,0:19:20.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, didn't you say something like this in order to stop him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.73,0:19:27.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Come back! If you don't do this properly and put an end to my life, you'll be next."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.23,0:19:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, the rest went like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.45,0:19:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If you stab me in the center of the "O" in Kuron, you're sure to succeed since it's right where my heart is."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.83,0:19:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramatsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was provoked by what you said...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.08,0:19:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And proceeded to stab the letter "0" with a knife...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.09,0:19:52.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not knowing that you had already placed the cigar case in the pocket where the letter "0" was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.38,0:19:54.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't give me this shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.05,0:19:55.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything you've said is just one lie after another!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.39,0:19:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If not, then where's some solid proof to back you up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.27,0:20:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yokomizo...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.35,0:20:03.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What time is it right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.02,0:20:06.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One minute before midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.07,0:20:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umetani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}..
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.98,0:20:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't we wait and see if the Aimuzu powers on once it's midnight?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.53,0:20:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If what you told us about not knowing the password is true, the chair will self-destruct.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.71,0:20:26.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Umetani{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.13,0:20:35.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's midnight!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.76,0:20:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good evening, President Umetani.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.52,0:20:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thank you, President, for your wise decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.15,0:20:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please make a huge profit off of my Aimuzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.90,0:20:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And may we never meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.74,0:20:56.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Farewell, President Umetani.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.12,0:21:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn..
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.51,0:22:41.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's good, Conan.\NNow work a little more on the shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.85,0:22:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It somehow feels like I'm being trampled.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.06,0:22:52.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle, that's exactly what I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.02,0:22:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, let's buy a massage chair!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.53,0:23:01.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to buy something that expensive, how about doing some work that actually provides an income?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.91,0:23:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't you feel sorry that Conan has to do all this hard work?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.25,0:23:11.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I said... I'll massage you if you'd prefer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.04,0:23:14.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.46,0:23:18.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, Ran! Please stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.88,0:23:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we start on the spine, you'll feel a lot more relaxed afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.68,0:23:25.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, stop resisting!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.19,0:23:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, now I'll go cook us a delicious dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.90,0:23:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today, we're going to eat a hamburger.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.36,0:23:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Scary...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.83,0:03:42.33,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,After all, it's somewhat troublesome being a one-man president when this kind of thing happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.63,0:07:59.92,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He always did whatever he wanted to...
